EncounterIntro: The adventuring duo find a fruit tree with numerous rare fruit hanging from its upper branches
PlayerAction: Spencer tries to shake the tree with all his might.
RewardFeedback: Spencer's efforts make several of the fruit fall. He will be able to sell these back in the village.
PunishFeedback: Spencer does not manage to shake any of the fruit loose. He hurts his shoulder in the process.

EncounterIntro: As the duo enter a forest they stumble upon a heavily worn wooden board that reads “forest map”.
PlayerAction: Jack relies on his intelligence to parse the details of the map.
RewardFeedback: Jack successfully deciphers the map. He finds a path that avoids nearby hazards.
PunishFeedback: Jack gets confused by the worn map. He leads the duo into a quicksand pit causing them to drop some valubles.

EncounterIntro: The duo stumbles upon a elvish merchant. The merchant says "solve my riddle to earn a prize or else pay me a token!"
PlayerAction: Spencer relies on his wit to make sense of the riddle.
RewardFeedback: Spencer solves the riddle. He is rewarded with a small silver trinket.
PunishFeedback: Spencer is unable to make sense of the riddle. He is obligated to pay the merchant.

EncounterIntro: A fissue connects the two sides of a valley.
PlayerAction: Jack tries to use his athleticism to jump across the fissure.
RewardFeedback: Jack successfully jumps the gap. He is able to secure a rope to throw back across.
PunishFeedback: Jack barely grabs on to the edge. He is able to climb up and secure a rope but is injured in the process.

EncounterIntro: An ancient statue stands before the adventurers. On it is etched an unfamiliar language.
PlayerAction: Jack tries to rely on his intelligence to decipher the language.
RewardFeedback: Jack is able to  decipher a set of instructions to a nearby cache. He is led to a cache of small gemstones.
PunishFeedback: Jack is unable to make sense of the language. He is left empty handed.

EncounterIntro: The duo enters a clearing where a formidable troll awaits. A sign nearby states, Defeat the troll to proceed.""
PlayerAction: Spencer charges forward. He swings his weapon with all his might.
RewardFeedback: Spencer parries the troll's counterattack and makes a critical hit. He defeats the troll with minimal injuries.
PunishFeedback: The troll proves resistant against Spencer’s attack and counters their attack. He suffers damage from several attacks before felling the troll.

EncounterIntro: As the duo continues they notice a shiny metal embedded in a nearby rock face.
PlayerAction: Jack picks up a nearby rock. He uses the rock to try to smash away some of the metal.
RewardFeedback: Jack is successful. He stores some of the ore to prospect later.
PunishFeedback: Jack accidentally bashes their hand in the process. He suffers an injury.

EncounterIntro: The duo stumbles across the camp of a known murdering bandit.
PlayerAction: Spencer tries to think of a clever way to subdue the bandit. He hides while pondering.
RewardFeedback: Spencer navigates a path behind the bandit. He hits them over the head with rock.
PunishFeedback: Spencer attempts to sneak behind the bandit. He is caught and is painfully struck before subduing the bandit.

EncounterIntro: The duo arrives a large rock tall enough to give a better view of the area.
PlayerAction: Jack tries to muscle his way up the rock.
RewardFeedback: Jack successfully climbs to the top of the rock. He spots a shortcut to a known hunting ground.
PunishFeedback: Jack was unable to clumb the rock. He falls on his shoulder and suffers an injury.

EncounterIntro: In the bandit camp, the players are presented with a locked ornate chest.
PlayerAction: Spencer relies on his wit to try to decipher the combination on the lock.
RewardFeedback: Spencer unlocks the chest revealing a pouch of gold inside. He puts the treasure in his pack for safekeeping.
PunishFeedback: Spencer triggers a trap and an arrow is launched at them. He suffers damage.

EncounterIntro: As the duo continue they stumble across a rabid dog. The dog begins chargins.
PlayerAction: Spencer attempts to overpower the charging dog using his pack to absorb the bite.
RewardFeedback: Spencer successfully overpowers the dog. He redirects the dog and shoves it down an steep adjacent hill.
PunishFeedback: Spencer is able to absorb the brunt of the attack and pushes the dog down an adjacent hill. He gets several scratches in the process.

EncounterIntro: As the duo continue their path is blocked by a dense and thorny mass of bushes.
PlayerAction: Jack attempts to slash at the branches with all his might.
RewardFeedback: Jack successfully cuts through the branches. He suffers no ill effects.
PunishFeedback: Jack is able to cut through after considerable effort. He suffers some injuries in the process.

EncounterIntro: The duo come across a tree strump with glowing mushrooms growing on top.
PlayerAction: Jack tries to rely on his intelligence to decipher the species of mushroom.
RewardFeedback: Jack recalls that these mushrooms have healing properties. He stores them in their pack to sell later.
PunishFeedback: Jack misremembers the mushroom's species. He is zapped by the mushroom's glow when they try to pick them.

EncounterIntro: The duo come across a set of track leading off the path
PlayerAction: Spencer attempts to be clever. He looks for clues to parse the direction of the tracks.
RewardFeedback: Spencer identies the direction of the tracks. He successfully avoids stepping on a nearby python in the process.
PunishFeedback: Spencer identies the direction of the tracks. He accidentally steps on a python and is bitten suffering an injury in the process.

EncounterIntro: A boar emerges from the nearby foliage.
PlayerAction: Jack attempts to strike the boar with all his strength.
RewardFeedback: Jack successfully strikes down the boar. He is able to reclaim some meat to sell later.
PunishFeedback: Jack wasn't strong enough to strike down the boar. He is tripped by the boar as it escapes suffering an injury in the process.

EncounterIntro: The duo come across a wagon stuck in the mud and a distressed villager.
PlayerAction: Spencer attempts to rely on his intelligence to find a solution.
RewardFeedback: Spencer was able to find a strong branch to lever the wagon out of the mud. He was rewarded with some gold coins.
PunishFeedback: Spencer was unable to think of a solution. He is thanked by the upset villager for trying….

EncounterIntro: The duo come across a forest gnome requesting aid to rescue their pet racoon from a tree.
PlayerAction: Spencer attempts to use his strength and athleticism to climb the tree.
RewardFeedback: Spencer was able to climb the tree and rescue the racoon.  He is rewarded with a few gemstones.
PunishFeedback: Spencer was unable to climb the tree and scares the racoon in the process. The gnome turns some of his valubles into rocks.

EncounterIntro: The duo come across two traveling mercenaries engaged in a heated argument about directions.
PlayerAction: Jack attempts to rely on his intelligence to decipher directions for the mercenaries.
RewardFeedback: Jack was able to successfully direct the travelers. He is rewarded with some gold coins.
PunishFeedback: Jack was unable to help and is punched for wasting the mercenary's time. He is bruised in the process.
